<TITLE> Govt appeals Hannan Shah bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 DHAKA, November 26 (bdnews24.com)  The government Monday appealed a High Court order granting BNP leader ASM Hannan Shah bail in a case that involves violations of emergency powers rules. Government counsel ASM Khalequzzaman told bdnews24.com the appeal would be heard Tuesday. The High Court granted Hannan Shah three weeks' bail in the case on November 22. Police filed a case with Tejgaon Police Station on November 7 against six people including Hannan Shah on charges of violating the EPR. Emergency rules were allegedly breached when rival BNP groups clashed near late president Ziaur Rahman's grave in Sher-e-Bangla Nagar. During the scuffle, former army chief retired lieutenant general Mahbubur Rahman was allegedly harassed while paying his respects at the grave. Hannan was arrested on November 7. A court ordered his detention for a month on November 8. bdnews24
